pddl.prompt:
You are the orchestrator. You will receive structured availability reports from multiple participants for Monday. The environment public information is:
{environment->public_information}
Here are the participant availability reports (you will be given them as inputs):
{pddl->input}
Your orchestrator goal is:
{agents->orchestrator->goal}
Integrate the availabilities, resolve any naming mismatches, and produce a cohesive PDDL domain and PDDL problem that encodes: participants, time slots (30-minute granularity between 09:00 and 17:00), busy constraints, and the goal of scheduling a single 30-minute meeting when all participants are free. Target the FastDownwards solver. Enclose the PDDL domain between <domain></domain> tags and the PDDL problem between <problem></problem> tags. Keep participant actions and any scheduling actions distinct and explicit.
